title: Epistomology 1
author: Striker2117
pages:
#- The fundamental fallacy of ordinary understanding is the delusion that the universe is reducible to simple substance, or—the more Hume-like view—that the content of human knowledge is limited to simple-substance-like, self-evident sense perceptions. 
#- This discredited outlook—whether it takes the naive mechanistic [form] or the equivalent mechanistic outlook of empiricism—is termed reductionism. All varieties of reductionism are formally premised on the fallacious assumption
#-  of formal logic, that the universe can be represented as discrete points interconnected by formal relations. 
~~Ronald Grundeswald; CEO of Grundescorp
